Write a PHP program to accept form input and display it using the POST method. 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<head> 
    <title>PHP Form</title> 
</head> 
<body> 
<h2>Simple Form</h2> 
<form method="POST"> 
    Name: <input type="text" name="name"><br><br> 
    Email: <input type="text" name="email"><br><br> 
    <input type="submit" value="Submit"> 
</form> 
<?php 
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") { 
    $name = $_POST['name']; 
    $email = $_POST['email']; 
    echo "<h3>Entered Details:</h3>"; 
    echo "Name: " . $name . "<br>"; 
    echo "Email: " . $email; 
} 
?> 
</body> 
</html> 
 
 
7.. Implement a PHP program for string manipulation (e.g., reverse, length, substring). 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<head> 
    <title>String Manipulation</title> 
</head> 
<body> 
<h2>String Manipulation</h2> 
<form method="POST"> 
    Enter String: <input type="text" name="str"><br><br> 
    <input type="submit" value="Submit"> 
</form> 
<?php 
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") { 
    $str = $_POST['str']; 
    echo "<h3>Results:</h3>"; 
    // Length 
    echo "Length: " . strlen($str) . "<br>"; 
    // Reverse 
    echo "Reverse: " . strrev($str) . "<br>"; 
    // Substring (first 5 characters) 
    echo "Substring (first 5 chars): " . substr($str, 0, 5); 
} 
?> 
</body> 
</html> 
Create a PHP script to store and display values in an array. 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<head> 
    <title>Array Input</title> 
</head> 
<body> 
<h2>Enter 3 Names</h2> 
<form method="POST"> 
    Name 1: <input type="text" name="name[]"><br><br> 
    Name 2: <input type="text" name="name[]"><br><br> 
    Name 3: <input type="text" name="name[]"><br><br> 
    <input type="submit" value="Submit"> 
</form> 
<?php 
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") { 
    $names = $_POST['name']; // array 
    echo "<h3>Names Entered:</h3>"; 
    foreach ($names as $n) { 
        echo $n . "<br>"; 
    } 
} 
?> 
</body> 
</html>